"Local women lost their clients."
Indonesian President Joko Widodo – nicknamed Jokowi – promised in his 2014 election campaign to address Papua’s injustices and human rights violations.
Papua consists of 29 districts, and this former carpenter won the vote in 27 districts, including Pania, on his way to Jakarta’s Presidential Palace.
But little has changed in Papua, and the locals feel betrayed.
