The remote Papua has little attention in the world.
In addition, restrictions on international news coverage remain strict.
Earlier this year, French journalists Franck Escudie and Basille Longchamp were expelled from Papua, although they had been granted a rare photographic license due to their inability to cooperate with local institutions.
According to Phelim Kine, Asia’s deputy director of Human Rights Watch, Jokowi has not kept his election promises, has not increased transparency and has not promoted development by removing restrictions on news coverage.
